                    <CHRONPROSE><NAME STANDARD="Le Prince de Beaumont, Jeanne">Jeanne Le Prince de
							Beaumont </NAME> published <TITLE TITLETYPE="MONOGRAPHIC">Le Magasin des
							enfants</TITLE>, a collection containing a first influential and
						literary formulation of the popular <TGENRE GENRENAME="FAIRYTALE">fairy story </TGENRE><TITLE TITLETYPE="ANALYTIC">Beauty and the Beast</TITLE>.<BIBCITS> <BIBCIT DBREF="65785" PLACEHOLDER="Zipes 125-6">125-6</BIBCIT> </BIBCITS></CHRONPROSE>
                </CHRONSTRUCT>
                <SHORTPROSE>
                    <P>The origins of this story lie in folk-tale and in the second-century text
							<TITLE TITLETYPE="MONOGRAPHIC">The Golden Ass</TITLE> by
							<NAME>Apuleius</NAME>. Its outlines are legible in several tales by
							<NAME>Marie-Catherine d'Aulnoy</NAME>. It became a drama by
							<NAME>Stéphanie-Félicité de Genlis </NAME> in 1785 and an opera by <NAME STANDARD="Marmontel, Jean-Francois">Marmontel</NAME> and <NAME STANDARD="Grtry, Andr">Grétry</NAME> in 1788.<BIBCITS> <BIBCIT PLACEHOLDER="Zipe 128-9" DBREF="65785">128-9</BIBCIT> </BIBCITS></P>
                </SHORTPROSE>
